caption: Delicious, great beer selection which you can still order togo. Can't wait for their patio to open!

Decent spot to get fried chicken. Options for chicken piece and sides are nice. A plate is good enough for a standard meal. The chicken itself isn't spicy but you can ask for sauce to add a bit of heat. Prices are reasonable and service is fairly quick. Lots of seating space so large groups wouldn't be a problem.

This is the definition of a dive. However, the food is SPECTACULAR. I can see why people had ordered so much food. The chicken is spicy but it is enjoyable. It is not so spicy that you can’t taste the chicken. It is crispy and crunchy but not overcooked. The presentation isn’t much. You are served on a paper plate with plastic products, but don’t let that detract you! This is an amazing spot. Stop in at Gus’. You won’t be mad that you did.
They need better chairs. The food is great!
Nice sit down joint. Good food good service...
Was in town for the C2E2 and wanted some local grub. Chicken was amazing.
The chicken was bomb
Best fried chicken.  Spicy (but not too spicy!). And crispy.  The meat melts in your mouths.  All sides are excellent!

The waitress was very pleasant and the potato salad was tasty but the chicken is on the dry side. Dark meat is supposed to have some juice. I noticed the skin is very dark and that's because it's over fried. Although not the best, it's not completely terrible. It would be worth another try if they could improve their chicken recipe. Thank you.
Fye(GOOD) CHICKEN😍

Amazing food, definitely recommend the house made potato salad (as you see by the tub) and the season on all the chicken is pretty good, personally I don't even taste any spiciness but it is definitely quite flavorful
3 wings with coleslaw and baked beans is my favorite spicy chicken

Pretty decent place to get fried chicken downtown. It's not the best fried chicken around, with the breading a bit lacking and not nearly as crispy as I'd like. That said, the chicken is juicy and a great deal considering the location. A 3-piece dark meat with 2 sides is plenty of food and will set you back only $12, compared to $15-20 lunches in the area which seem to be the norm.
Spiced perfectly, nice portions.
Food was prompt and  hot service great
Honestly, I've  had better. It's  good, but not $11 for a 3 piece good.  Once was enough.
Love this place!  Very tasty and juicy chicken!
It was good, I enjoyed it!
10 stars. If you know you know and if you don't, this fried chicken is better than your grandma's
Delicious!
Delicious Memphis hot and spicy fried chicken. Great sides too.

It’s not all that the chicken was cooked a lil longer than what it should had been. Thanks to the seasoning  an of course Louisiana hot sauce  on the chicken you avoid the crispy burnt taste of the skin.
Average

Delicious. My only complaint is that it's really pricey.

Came into town and visited this spot with a friend at her request. It's decent. Seem like a cool spot to go eat. To get great chicken isn't as easy as people think. Still say Popeye's got some of the best fried yard bird, but Gus isn't bad.
Wow! Do yourself a favor and eat here.

i am a fan of hole-in-the-wall eateries.  this is such a place.  The chicken was good, but what earned the review was the warm Chess Pie with ice-cream.   So simple and good!

Excellent food and service reasonably priced.  Food is made to order and atmosphere is unpretentious.
The food was awesome. Very fresh, very flavorful and the hostess was great. You guys are wonderful.👍👍

Been here for the second consecutive weekend now. It’s my thing now and every time I visit Chicago downtown, I eat here lol. I got half chicken and friend okra as sides. The chicken is super crispy outside and tender and juicy on the inside. The seasoning is not too bland or not too spicy. just perfect ! One of my most fav fried chicken !! The location is perfect and the service is great too!
Tender juicy spicy homemade gourmet great service
Great place to go if you gave a hankering for some fried food. Spicy fried chicken with a great coleslaw and baked beans. Loved the fried okra. Nice space.
I really enjoy the champagne & service chicken wise could have been spicer & crisper
Great chicken, nice service.

Being from Memphis, this meal brought me right back home for a minute. Of course the atmosphere is not quite like in the south (between all the tall buildings and all...) But the food is good. Waiters lack the southern slang, but that's ok for Chicago. Service was fast and friendly. Must have for visitors.
A true slice of the South. Just as good as the one in Memphis.  Chicken is hot and crispy,  mac and cheese oh so good, sweet tea, and pie. Yes, please!
They were really busy when we got there, but the staff took care of us as best they could. The chicken,baked beans,and cole slaw were very good. Try the green fried tomatoes! Cute atmosphere as well.
I enjoyed my meal in the late night after the Amanda Seals Show. Thanks for the sweet potato pie and ice cream!!!! Yummy
The food was average...not bad but not worth returning for either.
Food was insanely good... crispy and fresh fried chicken with excellent flavor. All of the sides were exceptional. Service was great and everyone was super friendly!

The chicken was very possibly the best I ever had. I had the sweet potato pie and it was also incredible. The sides were fine, me and my gf split a side of mac and cheese with our baked beans and slaw. The beer was reasonably priced. I would absolutely go back and have already told my family and loved ones.
Really enjoy this Restaurant, Tawanda our waitress gave us good service.  The first bite of the chicken surprised us on how spicy and hot it was.  But after that it was how great and juicy it tasted.
Nice comfort food. Place is a bit cold, but that would be my only complain... nice options for sides as well. Some days they serve chicken and waffles.

Never been to Tennessee but this place has really good fried chicken. So crispy and with a good kick to it. Pretty good value, although a bit simple. Side dishes were excellent as well. Hiding right over the bridge on the river. Friendly and good service.
Great service, so easy to access from Miracle Mile hotels.  Never a question about the chicken, it's Gus's FFS!
The chicken is Amazing!!!
Great experiance but no barbecue:c

We arrived later, closer to 11pm. Friendly staff, very patient with us being new the younger ones being young. Long story short: The chicken was very good and juicy. The Louisiana hot sauce was a very good complement to the chicken itself. The tenders were very juicy, but even the white meat breast was juicy.  We didn’t like the potato salad (personal preference to style, it wasn’t bad), or the beans (personal preference again, a bit too sweet for us) but the sides were well done. We liked the slaw, it’d probably be good on a (hint) chicken sandwich. The youngest had the grilled cheese, which she devoured.  All in all, a tasty bite to eat.
Okay, the chicken was amazing.   Enjoyed the greens, mac and cheese and the fried okra.   Will DEFINITELY return.   Making me hungry just thinking about it.   Yum!
The best in Chicago
Great service, great food, what's not to love?
Not bad. Just average.
This is the best friend chicken place I have visited in a long time. Must visit.
Food was good but give me some old school Harold's.

Gus’s is great. Just opened this location about 5 months ago. 30 franchised locations across the nation. Staff is extremely friendly. The wet chicken batter has all the spice and flavor mixed in. Dropped in 375 degree oil it comes out crisp. Watch the after burners on the spice. Will be sure to try any location I come across

Omg! Best chicken. Flavorful not overly greasy! Sides were not bad as well.  I hope it comes to Ohio soon like they said. We need it.

There is better in New Orleans, but so far, this is the best I've had in Chicago. Note: the slaw and beans are the default sides, and they're both pretty good.

Delicious !!

I swear this is the best fried chicken I've had outside of Atlanta... In Chicago? GO NOW!!!
The staff was very friendly and the chicken was pretty good!
If you enjoy great fried chicken - and cold beer - you’ll be so happy that you visited.

You know how much I love my fried chicken! Gus's rocks! In fact, their chicken's just as good as Harold's. But they beat Harold's in my mind by using a spicy batter, unlike Harold's, who just sticks to regular seasoned batter. They also have a great selection of sides, including greens, baked beans, mac and cheese, and of course, fries. And if you want to refresh with an ice cold beer, they've got you covered!

The fried chicken has some heat on it, due to the spices, which was very good; however, the chicken was barely "warm" temperature-wise instead of hot. This gave the impression that the chicken was not very fresh and it definitely tasted as such. The sides shown here is the mac and cheese, and the greens. The greens were not very good.
The chicken is delicious, im so happy they opened up another restaurant branch on State Street. Fulton Market is hard to get to but the restaurant on State is completely accessible.
Hands down the best dang chicken ever!

So good! All it needs to do is change the bread option to hush puppies.
Sandy and the ladies were amazing! Made my 1st experience unforgettable...... In a good way..... Not to mention, the chicken is SUPERB
What awesome friend chicken. A great amount of spice, too. Great potato salad and baked beans.
Good chicken and service. Diggin the rustic vibe
Not too good but can try once if u r a chicken lover
Excellent
The best fried chicken! Great service and delicious food without any pretentiousness.
We ate the original in Memphis, this one is just as good. Good food & good service.
The chicken is good. The service was a little lacking during the lunch rush.
Omg! I've tried the one by the fresh market...i fell in love.  I'm a chicken eater and if I say it's good.... it's good✊ I'll be stopping by sooner than later I hope.

Super delicious!! I wouldn't consider it hot and spicy, but rather just flavored. The sides that came with the meal, baked beans and coleslaw, was also very good, likewise the mac and cheese was also very good.
Excellent chicken !
Wish they had BBQ sauce to go with the tenders....ranch and honey mustard are the only sauce options :(.
No words it's just that good!
Keeps the feel of a southside chicken place, still ironing out some of the quirks of a new place. Chicken is pretty decent-remember this is a spicy chicken (but not that hot)
Allergic to peanuts. Didn't get to eat. So if you have a peanut allergy, skip this and Five Guys.

Dining room nice, comfortable. Staff friendly even though the waiter took my plate without asking and there was still food on the plate, wouldn't replace what he threw away. Food was decent for the area, kinda pricey still. Only afforable for people with big pockets still.

Best chicken I’ve had in my entire life. Amazing friendly service. I’m telling all my friends about this place. That breast and wing had more juicy well flavored meat than I am used to. I can’t wait to back for lunch!!! Keep up the great work!!!

I am delighted to be this Place’s first review. The service is amazing we were there 15 mins before close down for take out. We got some hot, fresh fried chicken. Being dark meat fans, the lovely gentleman behind the counter made some great recommendations. Their Mac n cheese, owh it’s the best. It’s stick to your teeth cheese (which for me is amazing). I can totally see this being a regular pick up joint for us given that we’re right down the street. In fact, my husband who adores fried chicken might like Gus’s more than Popeye’s for their spice level. So so good I didn’t get to take a picture 😛

River North can definitely use a good fried chicken place, and Gus’s fits the bill.  The place is surprisingly large. I was pleasantly surprised that table service was available.  Basically, you’re going to have chicken. You can have a breast, a thigh, a leg, a wing or any combination thereof. I had a half chicken so I could try them all. My favorite was the wing, which had the perfect crust to meat ration.  As you can tell from the name, the crust is spicy–not so hot you can’t taste anything else, but definitely spicy. It’s also nice and crisp, and not greasy (except maybe for the thigh).  The accompanying Cole slaw was delicious, with just the right hint of sweetness.  The beans were pretty good too.  Prices are good.  There’s a limited selection of beer, and probably the only reasonably priced bottle of Dom Perignon in all of River North!  Being brand new there were minor service and equipment issues, but overall a very good experience.

The food is good as expected but the staff is absolutely horrible. The second I walked in I felt bad vibes all around. I’ve never been here so I wanted to ask for a recommendation which led to a disgruntled employee saying to get the chicken. - Who woulda guessed?  I asked for an extra side of sauce for my order and instead they gave me zero sauce, not even the one included. Everyone needs sauce for chicken! Icing on the cake was when an employee yelled at me for taking too many napkins and said ”you already have enough napkins”  Quite possibly the rudest staff I’ve ever came across. All 3 employees working there were either having the worst day of their lives or just horrible at customer service. I received twice as much attitude as food on my visit for pretty basic requests: recommendations, sauce, napkins etc.

What a great place to get chicken. It's sort of a hidden location downtown, but wow. It has a great environment and is super convenient especially if you work in the area. This was some of the best fried chicken that I've ever had. The staff is super nice and helpful, the food came out pretty quickly, and the portion sizes are nothing to complain about. The menu is pretty simple, it's all fried chicken and it's all delicious. I had the three piece plate, but was told that the chicken tenders are just as good and will try them soon. Having Gus's so close to work is going to be a problem.....
